1. HTML Form in Template (home.html)
{% load static %}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Restaurant Homepage</title>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Search Bar -->
    <form method="get" action="{% url 'home' %}">
        <input
            type="text"
            name="q"
            placeholder="Search for menu items..."
            style="padding: 8px; width: 250px; border-radius: 5px; border: 1px solid #ccc;"
        >
        <button
            type="submit"
            style="padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 5px; border: none; background-color: #28a745; color: white;"
        >
            Search
        </button>
    </form>

</body>
</html>


2. Update URLconf (urls.py)
# urls.py
from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [
    path('', views.home_view, name='home'),
]


3. Handle the Query in Your View (views.py)
# views.py
from django.shortcuts import render

def home_view(request):
    query = request.GET.get('q')
    if query:
        print(f"User searched for: {query}")  # Just to show it's working

    return render(request, 'home.html', {})


Now, when a user types something and hits "Search", the page reloads and the terminal shows:
User searched for: pizza
